      <h2>Some facts about Sidney Crosby:</h2>
      <article id="tribute-info">
<p>Sidney Patrick Crosby (born August 7, 1987) is a Canadian professional ice hockey player who serves as captain of the Pittsburgh Penguins of the National Hockey League (NHL). Nicknamed "Sid the Kid" and dubbed "The Next One", Crosby was selected first overall by the Penguins in the 2005 NHL Entry Draft, and is widely regarded as one of the greatest hockey players of all time.</p>
        
<p>Internationally, Crosby has represented Canada on numerous occasions:</p>
        
        <ul>
          <li><u><strong>2005:</strong></u> Gold at the World Junior Championship.</li>
          <br>
          <li><u><strong>2010:</strong></u> Played for Team Canada at the Winter Olympics in Vancouver. Scored the gold-winning goal during overtime against the United States.</li>
          <br>
          <li><u><strong>2014:</strong></u> Captained Team Canada at the Winter Olympics and won his second consecutive Olympic gold medal.</li>
          <br>
          <li><u><strong>2015:</strong></u> Led Canada to gold in the World Champiionship in Prague.</li>
          <br>
          <li><u><strong>2016:</strong></u> Captained Canada to gold in the World Cup of Hockey and was elected MVP by unanimous vote.</li>
          <br>
        </ul>
        
      </article>
      
